Simple Scanner Privacy Policy
This privacy policy of the mobile application Simple Scanner for Android or IOS devices
        that was created by
TongSoft
            Information Co.,
            Ltd.
Hereinafter referred to as (TongSoft)
Your scanned documents
Your scanned documents are saved locally on your devices. Users are able to set up auto upload to
        cloud storage
        (Google Drive, Box, Dropbox or OneDrive) so that their data won't lost and they can access them anywhere. The
        upload process will run automatically when Simple Scanner app is in background. Simple Scanner requires App
        Folder permission only for cloud storage services. It means Simple Scanner only accesses (read, write and
        delete) files created by Simple Scanner app, our app can't access other user's data on their cloud service.
Sync documents in the cloud
We have added the function of synchronizing documents in the cloud. You need to register and log in to use it.
        You can synchronize your documents between multiple platforms and devices to ensure that the documents will not
        be lost. Regarding the automatic synchronization function, you can view it in the app. We use encryption
        protocols To protect your documents, documents are stored in Google cloud storage, and at the same time comply
        with Google's relevant policies and terms, you can use it with confidence, and if you have any questions, you
        can contact us at any time.
Login to Simple Scanner using Google account
Simple Scanner suggests users login to our system using Google account. User can use that account for all
        devices. Example: if account is upgraded to PRO, user can use that account to login to Simple Scanner on iOS.
        User will be charged only one time and use it forever with all his devices (both Android and iOS).
        The validation Google account process will be done by Google server, Simple Scanner
        will receive the result from
        Google server. On our server, each user has a record contains the basic information: email id (example:
        simple.scanner@outlook.com), account type (free or pro).
